y this could mean that there is something that is blocking it.";i:35;s:94:"It may be that it is being obstructed by a protruding nut misaligned cable or any other thing.";i:36;s:87:"Check the rollers tracks and hinges for anything that may cause the door to get jammed.";i:37;s:92:"16 May 2009 at 1149PM edited 30 November -1 at 100AM in In My Home includes DIY MoneySaving.";i:38;s:90:"Ive got an up and over garage door ie as it lifts the top goes in and the bottom goes out.";i:39;s:100:"Its always been a bit stiff when closing it I always need to kick the bottom a bit to get it closed.";i:40;s:52:"Did the usual today but kicked too hard at one side.";i:41;s:76:"Misalignment of or damage to the garage door tracks can be very problematic.";i:42;s:119:"If this is the case when you open your garage door it wont do so smoothly and in some cases may simply not open at all.";i:43;s:53:"Here are some other telltale signs of track problems.";i:44;s:88:"Gaps between the rollers and the rail components that are misshapen and a rubbing noise.";i:45;s:95:"Having jammed garage doors can be a real problem for all overhead garage door owners out there.";i:46;s:102:"Being in such a situation is not only troublesome but it can also leave your homes vulnerable as well.";i:47;s:159:"If you have no idea what to do when your garage door is jammed give your local garage door repair company a call and see what they can do about your situation.";i:48;s:128:"All garage doors are specially designed to move smoothly during operation ensuring the perfect balance when opening and closing.";i:49;s:133:"If your garage door is unstable during operation or when it is in the up position there is a significant risk that the door may fall.";i:50;s:92:"Stones and debris can become lodged in the garage door mechanism obstructing key components.";i:51;s:48:"This can prevent the door from closing properly.";i:52;s:171:"If you suspect an object is jamming your door carry out a brief inspection of the garage 